[1] Brazil (Bahia)
Date: Mon 27 Apr 2009
Source: G1 [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://g1.globo.com/Noticias/Brasil/0,,MUL1100451-5598,00-MAIS+DE+MIL+CASOS+DE+DENGUE+SAO+REGISTRADOS+NA+BAHIA.html>


The number of confirmed dengue cases have reached 55 483 in Bahia up
to 17 Apr of this year [2009], which represents a 220 percent
increase compared to the same period in 2008. Of this total, 47
people have died [of dengue].

These numbers were released on Monday [27 Apr 2009] by the
Secretariat of Health of Bahia. The municipalities of Jequie,
Itabuna, Porto Seguro, Ilheus, and Salvador had practically half of
the confirmed [dengue] illnesses. Of this total, 389 people were
victims of DHF (dengue hemorrhagic fever). According to the bulletin
, 82 percent of the municipalities in Bahia recorded dengue cases.

--
