******
[2] Brazil (Para)
Date: Tue 28 Apr 2009
Source: Diario do Para [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.diariodopara.com.br/noticiafull.php?idnot=40756>


According to the Endemic Coordination unit of Castanhal, of the 77
recorded dengue [cases] in the city, 19 were DHF. From January to
April [2009], with the increase in rainfall and the accumulation of
large amounts trash in the center and the periphery [of the city],
there was increased proliferation of the mosquito. According to the
Coordination unit, the disease tends to worsen in 2 situations: by
self-medication and when there is delay in receiving medical aid.

The Coordination of Endemics unit of the Secretariat of Health,
asserts that one of major challenges to be overcome are the many
wastelands [vacant lots] existing throughout the city. According to
the unit, a partnership was established with the Castanhal Department
of [Public] Works (Semob) to be sent information concerning such
land. The Semob should notify the owners. The population should also
be directed to not continue to discard trash on land that should,
indeed, be [kept] clean.

--
