[3] Brazil (national)
Date: Sat 2 May 2009
Source: Jornal Pequeno [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.jornalpequeno.com.br/2009/5/2/Pagina106878.htm>


The most recent totals released by the Ministry of Health in early
April [2009] said that throughout the country dengue [viruses]
infected 161 414 people. The number is low, as it does not include
the new data provided by the state secretariats of health. One
example is Bahia. In the totals of the federal government were 41 093
[dengue] cases. The government of Bahia said that it reached 54 165
cases [that number is somewhat higher now. See the report from Bahia,
above. - Mod.TY]

Projections of cases can exceed the mark of 200 000 in all the units
[states] of the federation and the Federal District. The 3 states
that have highest number of cases are Bahia (54 165), Minas Gerais
(35 290), and Espirito Santo (30 634); 84 deaths have been recorded.
More than half of these deaths, 47, were recorded in Bahia.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed@promedmail.org>

